<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFEinstein1905e">Einstein, Albert (1905e), "Does the Inertia of a Body Depend Upon Its Energy Content?", <i>Annalen der Physik</i> <b>18</b>: 639–641</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Does+the+Inertia+of+a+Body+Depend+Upon+Its+Energy+Content%3F&amp;rft.jtitle=Annalen+der+Physik&amp;rft.aulast=Einstein&amp;rft.aufirst=Albert&amp;rft.au=Einstein%2C+Albert&amp;rft.date=1905e&amp;rft.volume=18&amp;rft.pages=639%E2%80%93641&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Albert_Einstein"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>. This annus mirabilis paper on mass-energy equivalence was received 27 September.</li>
