<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFPaul_Arthur_Schilpp.2C_editor1951">Paul Arthur Schilpp, editor (1951). <i>Albert Einstein: Philosopher-Scientist, Volume II</i>. New York: Harper and Brothers Publishers (Harper Torchbook edition). pp.&#160;730–746.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Albert+Einstein%3A+Philosopher-Scientist%2C+Volume+II&amp;rft.aulast=Paul+Arthur+Schilpp%2C+editor&amp;rft.au=Paul+Arthur+Schilpp%2C+editor&amp;rft.date=1951&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B730%E2%80%93746&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Harper+and+Brothers+Publishers+%28Harper+Torchbook+edition%29&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Albert_Einstein"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> His non-scientific works include: <i>About Zionism: Speeches and Lectures by Professor Albert Einstein</i> (1930), "Why War?" (1933, co-authored by <a href="/wiki/Sigmund_Freud" title="Sigmund Freud">Sigmund Freud</a>), <i>The World As I See It</i> (1934), <i>Out of My Later Years</i> (1950), and a book on science for the general reader, <i><a href="/wiki/The_Evolution_of_Physics" title="The Evolution of Physics">The Evolution of Physics</a></i> (1938, co-authored by <a href="/wiki/Leopold_Infeld" title="Leopold Infeld">Leopold Infeld</a>).</li>
